---
const principles = [
  { k: "Tokens", t: "Token-driven architecture. One source of truth, themes as data, components that recolour without a rebuild." },
  { k: "Performance", t: "Performance is a feature. Tight budgets, measured every build, because speed is part of the design." },
  { k: "Accessibility", t: "Accessible by default. Contrast, keyboard paths, and motion preferences, never bolted on at the end." },
  { k: "Tooling", t: "Tooling that compounds. Figma to code pipelines and AI assistants that surface the system where people work." },
];
---
<section id="approach" class="chapter">
  <div class="chapter-inner">
    <h2 class="chapter-headline" data-split>How I work</h2>
    <p class="chapter-lead">
      I lead design systems that hold up across teams and brands, and I treat the system itself
      as the product: the page you are reading is one.
    </p>
    <ul class="principles" data-stagger>
      {principles.map((p) => (
        <li class="principle">
          <span class="principle-k">{p.k}</span>
          <span class="principle-t">{p.t}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
